// Code signing configuration.
//
// Ad-hoc by default ("-") so CI and contributors build with no certificate.
//
// For a STABLE local identity — so macOS Accessibility and Keychain grants
// persist across rebuilds instead of breaking every time the ad-hoc CDHash
// changes — create a git-ignored file next to this one called
// `Signing.local.xcconfig` containing, for example:
//
//     CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = OpenDictation Dev
//
// (where "OpenDictation Dev" is a self-signed Code Signing certificate you
// create once in Keychain Access → Certificate Assistant → Create a
// Certificate). The optional include below picks it up when present.

CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = -

#include? "Signing.local.xcconfig"
